name: Unitersity of Baltimore Hospital

name: Maryland Renaissance Festival
directions: There are a few, but if you walk straight in through the gates and keep to the left those would be to closest ones to the entrance.
comment:
Need to be attending the festival in order to use toilet. (This means purchasing a ticket, so don't try to use the toilet here just in passing on the highway)

The only restrooms are gender neutral porta potties. Bring your own hand sanitizer as they sometimes run out. Usually only opened from late August until late October.

name: Good Life Organic Market
directions:
Women's room is in the back just past the kitchen.
Men's room is a little further back, around the corner near the back door.
comment:
Staff is extremely friendly. 
You don't need to buy anything, they'll just let you use the toilet.
There is never a line here.
The male owner will often use the women's room just because the men's room is already full. They literally won't think twice about anyone using whichever room.

Owners are also trans-friendly. 
This is a safe place and if you want to talk to them about supplements to compliment your transition, you can talk to them about it.
If you want supplement advice ask up front for Issac, Annie or Michelle. :)

name: Anne Arundel Community College Nurse's Office
directions:
Closest parking lot is Lot A.
Walk through the cafeteria and towards the bookstore. It will be in the hallway between the two on your right.
comment: They supply you with free tampons and condoms there as well if you need them. They are in the open and you don't have to ask for them.

name: Whitman-Walker Health
comment:
This an lgbt+ safe medical center.
You are safe here.
